Since $\goldE{\dfrac{1}{2}}$ equals $\goldE{\dfrac{2}{4}}$, we can add.

$\begin{align}
11 +  \left({\dfrac{1}{4}}+\goldE{\dfrac{1}{2}}\right) &= 11 +  \left({\dfrac{1}{4}}+\goldE{\dfrac{2}{4}}\right)\\\\
&= 11+\dfrac{3}{4}\\\\
&= 11\dfrac{3}{4}
\end{align}$

Since $\goldE{\dfrac{2}{2}}$ equals $\goldE{1}$, we can add for the total volume.

$\begin{align}
15+\dfrac{3}{4}+12+\goldE{\dfrac{2}{2}} &= 15+\dfrac{3}{4}+12+\goldE{1}\\\\
&=(15+12+1)+\dfrac{3}{4}\\\\
&=28\dfrac{3}{4}
\end{align}$
